---
import { getPublishedPosts } from "../lib/blog";
import { formatDateLong, toISODateString } from "../lib/date";

const posts = await getPublishedPosts();
const blogPostCount = posts.length;
const mostRecentBlogPost = posts[0];
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <title>Carter | A developer from Utah</title>
    <style>
      @layer reset {
        * {
          margin: 0;
          padding: 0;
          box-sizing: border-box;
        }
        h1,
        h2,
        h3 {
          font-size: initial;
        }
      }
      /* Variable fonts usage:
      :root { font-family: "Inter", sans-serif; }
      @supports (font-variation-settings: normal) {
        :root { font-family: "InterVariable", sans-serif; font-optical-sizing: auto; }
      } */
      @font-face {
        font-family: InterVariable;
        font-style: normal;
        font-weight: 100 900;
        font-display: swap;
        src: url("InterVariable.woff2") format("woff2");
      }
      @font-face {
        font-family: InterVariable;
        font-style: italic;
        font-weight: 100 900;
        font-display: swap;
        src: url("InterVariable-Italic.woff2") format("woff2");
      }
      .inline-avatar {
        height: 1lh;
        width: 1lh;
        display: inline-block;
        margin-inline-end: 0.1225rem;
        border-radius: 100%;
        vertical-align: text-bottom;
      }
      :root {
        scrollbar-gutter: stable;
      }
      body {
        font-family: "InterVariable", sans-serif;
        font-optical-sizing: auto;
        min-height: 100svh;
        display: grid;
        grid-template:
          [top-gutter-start] auto
          [top-gutter-end content-row-start] min-content
          [content-row-end bottom-gutter-start] auto
          [bottom-gutter-end] /
          [left-gutter-start] minmax(1rem, auto)
          [left-gutter-end content-col-start] minmax(min-content, 65ch)
          [content-col-end right-gutter-start] minmax(1rem, auto)
          [right-gutter-end];

        > * {
          grid-area: content-row-start / content-col-start / content-row-end /
            content-col-end;
        }
      }
      .stack {
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        gap: 1lh;
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <main class="stack">
      <section>
        <p>
          <strong>
            <img
              class="inline-avatar"
              src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg' viewBox='0 0 64 64'%3E%3Crect width='64' height='64' rx='32' fill='%23d9d9d9'/%3E%3Ccircle cx='32' cy='25' r='11' fill='%23888888'/%3E%3Cpath d='M14 56c2.5-10 9.5-17 18-17s15.5 7 18 17' fill='%23888888'/%3E%3C/svg%3E"
              alt="A headshot of Carter"
            />Carter McBride.
          </strong>
          He's a developer from Utah. Carter considers himself a minimalist. He's
          written a lot of JavaScript. Right now, he works at <strong
            ><img
              class="inline-avatar"
              src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg' viewBox='0 0 64 64'%3E%3Crect width='64' height='64' rx='32' fill='%23f03c00'/%3E%3Cpath d='M16 48 28 16h8l12 32h-8l-2.5-8h-11L24 48h-8Zm13-15h6l-3-10-3 10Z' fill='white'/%3E%3C/svg%3E"
              alt="The logo for Adobe"
            />Adobe</strong
          > on the <a href="https://github.com/adobe/alloy">AEP Web SDK,</a> a data
          collection and personalization library that runs on many of the world's
          biggest websites and storefronts.
        </p>
      </section>
      <section>
        <p>
          Some of Carter's projects are
          <a href="https://yazzy.carter.works">Yazzy</a> (a webapp to bring reader
          mode to any website),
          <a href="https://carterworks.github.io/rss-reader/">
            his personal RSS reader,
          </a> a small
          <a href="https://github.com/carterworks/substack-to-epub">
            Substack-to-epub scraper
          </a>, and his collection of
          <a href="https://tools.carter.works/"> tools. </a>
        </p>
      </section>
      <section>
        <p>
          He can be followed on <a href="https://github.com/carterworks"
            >GitHub,</a
          >
          <a href="https://mastodon.social/@literallyacar">Mastodon,</a>
          <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/thatcartermcbride/">LinkedIn</a>,
          and
          <a href="https://steamcommunity.com/id/CobraLaserFace/home">Steam.</a>
        </p>
      </section>
      <section>
        He has written {blogPostCount}
        <a href="/blog/">blog post{blogPostCount === 1 ? "" : "s"}.</a> The most recent
        was <a href={`/blog/${mostRecentBlogPost.id}/`}
          ><q>{mostRecentBlogPost.data.title}</q></a
        >
        and it was written on <time
          datetime={toISODateString(mostRecentBlogPost.data.pubDate)}
        >
          {formatDateLong(mostRecentBlogPost.data.pubDate)}
        </time>. You can get updates <a href="/blog/feed.xml">via RSS.</a>
      </section>
    </main>
  </body>
</html>
